        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(config): add XDG and GOG path overrides",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nThis PR implements the #621/#622 path model as one change:\n\n- Add kind-aware config/data/state/cache path resolution with `GOG_HOME`, per-kind `GOG_CONFIG_DIR`, `GOG_DATA_DIR`, `GOG_STATE_DIR`, `GOG_CACHE_DIR`, and global `--home`.\n- Move new auth metadata, file-keyring data, service-account keys, tracking state, Gmail watch state, and backup/cache state to the correct kind-specific roots.\n- Preserve legacy reads for normal migration, but keep explicit `GOG_HOME`/per-kind overrides isolated so CI, containers, and agents do not silently import host secrets/state.\n- Keep Drive/Gmail download defaults unchanged unless the command already has its own output flag.\n- Document path precedence, XDG behavior, compatibility rules, and container/systemd usage.\n\n## Compatibility notes\n\n- Relative `GOG_*_DIR` and `--home` values are rejected; relative XDG values are ignored per XDG expectations.\n- Legacy OAuth credentials, service-account keys, file-keyring directories, tracking config, backup config, and Gmail watch files remain readable when no explicit gog-specific override is active.\n- Existing legacy file-keyring secrets remain authoritative when both old and new data roots exist, so migration does not hide stored client secrets.\n- Explicit gog-specific roots intentionally skip legacy secret/state fallback to preserve sandbox isolation.\n- `--home` applies before parser/help rendering even when placed after a subcommand.\n\n## Proof\n\n- `make ci`\n- `go test ./internal/config ./internal/secrets ./internal/cmd ./internal/googleapi ./internal/backup ./internal/tracking`\n- `make lint`\n- `GOOS=windows GOARCH=amd64 go test -c ./internal/tracking -o /tmp/gogcli-tracking-windows.test.exe`\n- `GOOS=windows GOARCH=amd64 .tools/golangci-lint run ./internal/tracking`\n- GitHub Actions PR CI run 26291047143: `test`, `worker`, `windows`, and `darwin-cgo-build` all green\n- Live smoke: isolated `GOG_HOME` writes credentials metadata to `GOG_HOME/data`, config path to `GOG_HOME/config`, keeps `client_secret` out of metadata, and lists the keyring-backed client\n- Live smoke: legacy credentials in the old config dir still list and remove when no explicit data override is set\n- Autoreview: `/Users/steipete/Projects/agent-scripts/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode branch --base origin/main` clean, no accepted/actionable findings\n\nCloses #621.\nCloses #622.\n\nThanks @alexminza for the original proposal and direction.\n",
        "branch": "feat/xdg-gog-home-paths",
